The people of '''Edda''', also known as the '''Edda Egbebu''', are a [[People group|sub-group]] of the [[Igbo people]] in south-eastern [[Nigeria]].<ref name="Staurt96">{{cite book|first=James Stuart |last=Olson |title=The Peoples of Africa: An Ethnohistorical Dictionary |publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group |page=234 |year=1996 |isbn=0313279187 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MdaAdBC-_S4C&pg=PA234}}</ref> The land and people of Edda have been constitutionally designated the present day [[Afikpo South]] [[Local government areas of Nigeria|Local Government Area]] of [[Ebonyi state|Ebonyi State]], [[Nigeria]].

