{{Infobox Ethnic group |group = Pakistanis in Lebanon |image = |caption = |population = 700<ref name="OPF"/> (as of ''2005'') |popplace = |langs = [[Urdu]] {{·}} [[Arabic language|Arabic]] ([[Lebanese Arabic]]) |rels = }}
'''Pakistanis in Lebanon''' are over 700.<ref name="OPF">{{citation|publisher=Ministry of Labour, Manpower, and Overseas Pakistanis|publication-place=Islamabad|title=Year Book, 2004&ndash;2005|accessdate=2009-09-19}}</ref> <ref>[http://www.mofa.gov.pk/lebanon/contents.aspx?type=statements&id=1 EMBASSY OF PAKISTAN IN LEBANON] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318003636/http://www.mofa.gov.pk/lebanon/contents.aspx?type=statements&id=1 |date=2012-03-18 }}, [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Pakistan)]]. Retrieved May 2011</ref> They are comparatively smaller than other [[Pakistanis in the Middle East|Pakistani diaspora communities in the Middle East]], and form a part of the much larger and mostly working-class South Asian population in the country, consisting of [[Sri Lankans in Lebanon|Sri Lankans]] and [[Indians in Lebanon|Indians]].
Many of them are illegal migrants from rural backgrounds who work as labourers in factories, private shops and the local construction industry.<ref name="a">{{cite news|url=http://www.mofa.gov.pk/lebanon/contents.aspx?type=contents&id=2|title=CONSULAR SERVICES|work=Embassy of Pakistan in Lebanon}}</ref> Members of the community undertake and organise participation in various cultural and national events each year to celebrate their [[Pakistan]]i heritage.<ref name="a"/><ref>[http://www.mofa.gov.pk/lebanon/contents.aspx?type=statements&id=6 PAKISTAN CULTURAL SHOW IN BEIRUT] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111020123747/http://www.mofa.gov.pk/lebanon/contents.aspx?type=statements&id=6 |date=2011-10-20 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.mofa.gov.pk/lebanon/contents.aspx?type=statements&id=5 NATIONAL DAY CELEBRATIONS] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111020123726/http://www.mofa.gov.pk/lebanon/contents.aspx?type=statements&id=5 |date=2011-10-20 }}</ref> There is also a local Lebanese Pakistani Friendship Association.<ref>[http://www.lepafa.com/ The Lebanese Pakistani Friendship Association] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110202132836/http://lepafa.com/ |date=2011-02-02 }}</ref>
