{{Infobox Ethnic group | group = Turks in Serbia | population = *'''647''' (2011 census)<ref>[http://webrzs.stat.gov.rs/WebSite/userFiles/file/Aktuelnosti/Etnicke_zajednice_sa_manje_od_2000_pripadnika_i_dvojako_izjasnjeni.pdf Попис становништва, домаћинстава и станова 2011. у Републици Србији: Становништво према националној припадности - „Остали“ етничке заједнице са мање од 2000 припадника и двојако изјашњени]</ref> *'''2,194''' Turkish nationals (2009)<ref>{{cite web|author=Çalışma ve Sosyal Güvenlik Bakanlığı|title=YURTDIŞINDAKİ VATANDAŞLARIMIZLA İLGİLİ SAYISAL BİLGİLER (31.12.2009 tarihi itibarıyla)|url=http://www.csgb.gov.tr/csgbPortal/diyih.portal?page=yv&id=1|accessdate=2011-09-27|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310234552/http://www.csgb.gov.tr/csgbPortal/diyih.portal?page=yv&id=1|archivedate=2012-03-10|df=}}</ref> | caption = | popplace = [[Belgrade]], [[Sandzak]] | langs = [[Turkish language|Turkish]], [[Serbian language|Serbian]] | rels = [[Sunni Islam]] | related = }}
'''Turks in Serbia''', also known as '''Serbian Turks''' are people of [[Turkish people|Turkish]] ancestry present in [[Serbia]]. Turks have lived on this territory since the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] period. The Turkish minority has traditionally lived in the urban areas of Serbia, however in 1830, when the [[Principality of Serbia]] was granted autonomy, many Turks emigrated as "[[Muhacir|muhacirs]]" (refugees) to [[Turkey]] and by 1862 almost all of the remaining Turks left [[Central Serbia]], including 3,000 from [[Belgrade]].<ref name="Minahan">{{citation |last=Vuletić|first=Aleksandra|year=2012|url=http://www.demogr.mpg.de/papers/working/wp-2012-018.pdf|title=Censuses in 19th century Serbia: inventory of preserved microdata|place=|publisher=Max Planck Institute for Demographic Research|page=7}}</ref> According to the 2011 census only 647 people declared themselves as Turks, though this does not include the [[Turks in Kosovo|Turkish minority in Kosovo]].<ref>[http://webrzs.stat.gov.rs/WebSite/userFiles/file/Aktuelnosti/Etnicke_zajednice_sa_manje_od_2000_pripadnika_i_dvojako_izjasnjeni.pdf Попис становништва, домаћинстава и станова 2011. у Републици Србији: Становништво према националној припадности - „Остали“ етничке заједнице са мање од 2000 припадника и двојако изјашњени]</ref>
